              <dt>Type:</dt>
              <dd>number or categorical coordinate string</dd>
            </dl>
            <p>
              Sets the size of each y axis bin. Default behavior: If `nbinsy` is 0 or omitted, we choose a nice round bin size such that the number of bins is about the same as the typical number of samples in each bin. If `nbinsy` is provided, we choose a nice round bin size giving no more than that many bins. For date data, use milliseconds or "M&lt;n&gt;" for months, as in `axis.dtick`. For category data, the number of categories to bin together (always defaults to 1).
            </p>
          </div>
        </details>
