<details>
  <summary>
    26. Volume traces
  </summary>
  <div style="margin-left: 22px">
    <p>
      A volume trace is an object with the key "type" equal to "volume" (i.e. {"type": "volume"}) and any of the keys listed below. Draws volume trace between iso-min and iso-max values with coordinates given by four 1-dimensional arrays containing the `value`, `x`, `y` and `z` of every vertex of a uniform or non-uniform 3-D grid. Horizontal or vertical slices, caps as well as spaceframe between iso-min and iso-max values could also be drawn using this trace.
    </p>
    <p>
      <details>
        <summary>
          autocolorscale
        </summary>
        <div style="margin-left: 22px">
          <dl>
            <dt>Parent:</dt>
            <dd>data[type=volume]</dd>
            <dt>Type:</dt>
            <dd>boolean</dd>
            <dt>Default:</dt>
            <dd>true</dd>
          </dl>
          <p>
            Determines whether the colorscale is a default palette (`autocolorscale: true`) or the palette determined by `colorscale`. In case `colorscale` is unspecified or `autocolorscale` is true, the default palette will be chosen according to whether numbers in the `color` array are all positive, all negative or mixed.
          </p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>
          caps
        </summary>
        <div style="margin-left: 22px">
          <dl>
            <dt>Parent:</dt>
            <dd>data[type=volume]</dd>
            <dt>Type:</dt>
            <dd>object containing one or more of the keys listed below.</dd>
            <dt>Default:</dt>
            <dd>true</dd>
          </dl>
          <p>
            Sets the fill ratio of the `slices`. The default fill value of the x `slices` is 1 meaning that they are entirely shaded. On the other hand Applying a `fill` ratio less than one would allow the creation of openings parallel to the edges.
          </p>
        </div>
